pullRequest.title: Enable SSLSession - Query GetChannelInfo / GetPreliminaryChannelInfo / InvalidateSession
pullRequest.bodyText:
This PR adds most of the information for SSLSession stuff:

A bunch of new enums for types from NSS (SSLKEAType, SSLNamedGroup, SSLAuthType, SSLCipherAlgorithm, SSLCompressionMethod, SSLMACAlgorithm, and SSLSignatureScheme).
Adds wrappers for the two return structs from NSS: SSLChannelInfo and SSLPreliminaryChannelInfo.
Adds the getters into org.mozilla.jss.nss.SSL: SSL.GetChannelInfo and SSL.GetPreliminaryChannelInfo.
Adds the SSL.InvalidateSession helper to allow the server to invalidate client sessions when necessary.
Adds a basic functionality test to make sure everything is wired up correctly.

When #150 and this PR are both merged, a new PR  (#434) will be opened with enables SSLSession in the existing JSSEngine implementations.

commit.message:
Add SSLChannelInfo, SSLPreliminaryChannelInfo

These two types are the results of two nss.SSL calls;
SSLPreliminaryChannelInfo contains the same information as
SSLChannelInfo, with added members to check if a field has been
populated by the respective NSS call. This occurs when the SSL handshake
isn't yet complete.

Signed-off-by: Alexander Scheel <ascheel@redhat.com>

Add SSL_GetChannelInfo, SSL_GetPreliminaryChannelInfo

Signed-off-by: Alexander Scheel <ascheel@redhat.com>

Add tests for SSL_GetChannelInfo, SSL_GetPreliminaryChannelInfo

Signed-off-by: Alexander Scheel <ascheel@redhat.com>

Add SSL_InvalidateSession

This allows the caller to invalidate the current session on a SSLFDProxy
instance.

Signed-off-by: Alexander Scheel <ascheel@redhat.com>
